s an exception running in embedded mode, and runs fine in network mode.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=m_fuchs","name":"m_fuchs","emailAddress":"markus dot fuchs at sun dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Markus Fuchs","active":true},"created":"2006-07-12T02:17:18.000+0000","updated":"2006-07-12T02:17:18.000+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12345796/comment/12421943","id":"12421943","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=djd","name":"djd","emailAddress":"djd at apache dot org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Daniel John Debrunner","active":true},"body":"java.lang.Short is not a valid object mapping for SMALLINT, JDBC defines the mapping as java.lang.Integer. The bug is with the network client not the embedded.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=djd","name":"djd","emailAddress":"djd at apache dot org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Daniel John Debrunner","active":true},"created":"2006-07-18T20:27:28.000+0000","updated":"2006-07-18T20:27:28.000+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12345796/comment/12424238","id":"12424238","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=kmarsden","name":"kmarsden","emailAddress":"kmarsdenderby at sbcglobal dot net","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Kathey Marsden","active":true},"body":"This one really has to be fixed in a feature release and better sooner than later since it may affect existing applications. I'd call this Normal +\r\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=kmarsden","name":"kmarsden","emailAddress":"kmarsdenderby at sbcglobal dot net","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Kathey Marsden","active":true},"created":"2006-07-29T00:06:09.000+0000","updated":"2006-07-29T00:06:09.000+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12345796/comment/12424240","id":"12424240","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=djd","name":"djd","emailAddress":"djd at apache dot org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Daniel John Debrunner","active":true},"body":"Not a bug, java.lang.Short is not a valid mapping to any type in JDBC","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=djd","name":"djd","emailAddress":"djd at apache dot org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Daniel John Debrunner","active":true},"created":"2006-07-29T00:17:26.000+0000","updated":"2006-07-29T00:17:26.000+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12345796/comment/12424612","id":"12424612","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=m_fuchs","name":"m_fuchs","emailAddress":"markus dot fuchs at sun dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Markus Fuchs","active":true},"body":"Hi Daniel,\r\n\r\n1) \" java.lang.Short is not a valid object mapping for SMALLINT\":\r\n\r\nWhy do I get the same exception on setObject(int parameterIndex, Object x) if I create the table w/ an INTEGER column for SHORT_VAL?\r\n\r\n2) \"java.lang.Short is not a valid mapping to any type in JDBC\":\r\n\r\nDoes that mean that classes having a \"Short\" field can not be mapped to the database? \r\nAlso, why does stmnt.setShort(1, Short.valueOf(\"0\")) work in this case?\r\n\r\nPlease consider re-opening this issue.\r\n\r\n-- markus.\r\n\r\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=m_fuchs","name":"m_fuchs","emailAddress":"markus dot fuchs at sun dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Markus Fuchs","active":true},"created":"2006-07-31T19:02:04.000+0000","updated":"2006-07-31T19:02:04.000+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12345796/comment/12424621","id":"12424621","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=djd","name":"djd","emailAddress":"djd at apache dot org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Daniel John Debrunner","active":true},"body":"Markus wrote:\r\n \"Also, why does stmnt.setShort(1, Short.valueOf(\"0\")) work in this case? \"\r\n\r\nBecause that's part of the JDBC api, convert a Java primitive short to a SMALLINT value and send it to the database.\r\n\r\nWhat you are asking for is a non-standard extension to JDBC, accepting java.lang.Short values to be valid input for setObject,\r\nthat's against the Derby charter. Much the same as it would be non-standard to accept  java.util.Date for a DATE column.\r\n\r\n\r\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=djd","name":"djd","emailAddress":"djd at apache dot org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Daniel John Debrunner","active":true},"created":"2006-07-31T19:30:39.000+0000","updated":"2006-07-31T19:30:39.000+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12345796/comment/12424627","id":"12424627","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=m_fuchs","name":"m_fuchs","emailAddress":"markus dot fuchs at sun dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Markus Fuchs","active":true},"body":"This behavior is apparantly implemented by many major database vendors, e.g. Oracle, SQLServer, Sybase, and the Derby network server. Because it's undefined by the JDBC spec doesn't mean that it *must* not be provided for user convenience. ","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=m_fuchs","name":"m_fuchs","emailAddress":"markus dot fuchs at sun dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Markus Fuchs","active":true},"created":"2006-07-31T19:51:24.000+0000","updated":"2006-07-31T19:51:24.000+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12345796/comment/12428649","id":"12428649","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=lancea","name":"lancea","emailAddress":"lance dot andersen at sun dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Lance Andersen","active":true},"body":"This behavior is expected to work correctly in JDBC.  The JDB C 4.0 spec has clarified this, ,but it is expected that it would work with any JDBC release.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=lancea","name":"lancea","emailAddress":"lance dot andersen at sun dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Lance Andersen","active":true},"created":"2006-08-17T13:24:50.000+0000","updated":"2006-08-17T13:24:50.000+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12345796/comment/12428675","id":"12428675","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rhillegas","name":"rhillegas","emailAddress":"rhillegas at apache dot org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10